The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 07 September is 69,928 (8,059.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 02 September, there were 2,247 new confirmed cases (259.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 August, there were 2,419 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 7% (172 fewer cases).
